<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Florida Woman Kills Stalker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HEATHROW, Fla. (AP) -- A greenskeeper who stalked a woman for  
months was shot and killed by the woman after he entered her home 
with a handgun and rope. 
</P>
<P>
	Donald Cook had repeatedly called Elizabeth MaGruder, spying on  
her with binoculars and skulking behind bushes as she golfed. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, he entered her home in an upscale gated community.  
Cook pulled a .25-caliber handgun from his waist and aimed it at 
Mrs. MaGruder's husband. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. MaGruder, 50, ran to a linen closet and got a gun. When  
Cook burst through the door, she fired her .38-caliber revolver 
once at close range and hit him in the chest, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Cook fired back five times, hitting Mrs. MaGruder in the abdomen  
and wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. MaGruder was listed in stable condition Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Seminole County Sheriff Don Eslinger said Tuesday that Mrs.  
MaGruder acted in self-defense and would not be charged. 
</P>
<P>
	Cook, 50, had been fired six months ago from Heathrow Country  
Club after Mrs. MaGruder complained about his constant phone calls. 
Mrs. MaGruder had hired Cook to work on her yard last year, but she 
stopped using him when she became uncomfortable with his attention, 
Eslinger said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
