<HEADLINE> Publisher Gets Auto Show Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The publisher of Motor Trend and Hot Rod  
magazines has acquired the world's leading new-car auto show 
management firm. 
</P>
<P>
	EMAP Petersen Inc., a major special interest magazine publisher  
with more than 160 publications, announced Monday it acquired 
Liberty Management Corp. and its subsidiary Liberty Productions 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Harrisburg, Pa.-based Liberty stages auto shows across the  
nation, including giants like the California International Auto 
Show in Anaheim, the Florida International New Car Show in Tampa 
and the Arizona International Auto Show in Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial details weren't disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	``We are impressed with the way in which Liberty has developed  
and mastered an efficient auto show production template and play to 
continue to expand the number of shows Liberty produces in key 
markets,'' said James D. Dunning Jr., chairman of EMAP Petersen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
