<HEADLINE> Sele Won't Start Because of Flu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Texas Rangers pitcher Aaron Sele was scratched  
from his scheduled start against the Chicago White Sox on Tuesday 
night because of the flu. 
</P>
<P>
	Esteban Loaiza, who has made 10 relief appearances this year,  
made his first start of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Sele, 3-3 with a 4.54 ERA, is the last Texas player to come down  
with the flu. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had that,'' manager Johnny Oates said. ``There were about  
four days I didn't want to sit on the bench, let alone pitch.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Loaiza, has a 6.75 ERA in 21 1-3 innings of relief. He's allowed  
a run in nine of his 10 relief appearances, and given up seven in 
his last four games. 
</P>
<P>
	Loaiza was a starter when the Rangers acquired him from  
Pittsburgh last summer. He went 3-6 with a 5.40 ERA in 14 starts 
for Texas. He also started four games in spring training this year, 
going 0-1 with an 8.10 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Clark is scheduled to pitch Wednesday and Mike Morgan on  
Thursday. 
</P>
