<HEADLINE> Ikea Recalls Toy After Choking Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) -- The Ikea home and accessories company  
is recalling a stacking-rings toy after a 5-year-old child choked 
to death on a ball that came with it. 
</P>
<P>
	The toy, called the Mula ring pyramid, consists of brightly  
colored rings that are to be stacked on a dowel. The smallest piece 
is a ball about 1.5 inches in diameter. 
</P>
<P>
	Ikea issued the worldwide recall Tuesday after receiving a  
report that a child had choked to death when the ball became lodged 
in his throat. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fatal accident occurred in the beginning of January this  
year in a European country; in agreement with the boy's family I 
will not say what country,'' Eva-Carin Banka-Johnsson of Ikea's 
children's division told the Swedish news agency TT. 
</P>
</TEXT>
