<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	Tyco International, up 3 1/4 at 87 7/8.  
</P>
<P>
	Goldman Sachs upgraded the stock to its ``recommended'' list  
from ``outperform.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Motorola, up 4 at 85 7/8.  
</P>
<P>
	A group of present and former executives disclosed a $1.6  
billion offer to buy the company's semiconductor components unit. 

</P>
<P>
	Sunbeam, up 1 1/8 at 8 5/8.  
</P>
<P>
	Friedman Billings Ramsey began coverage of the small-appliance  
maker with a rating of ``market perform.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Empire District Electric Co., up 4 1/4 at 25 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
	UtiliCorp United Inc., down 1/4 at 23 15/16.  
</P>
<P>
	UtiliCorp agreed to acquire Empire in a stock and cash deal  
valued at $800 million, including the assumption of debt. 

</P>
<P>
	Comdisco, up 3 5/16 at 27 3/16.  
</P>
<P>
	U.S. Bancorp Piper Jaffray reiterated a strong buy rating on the  
company, which remarkets IBM-compatible computers. Piper Jaffray 
said the company's recent expansion efforts ``signal the company 
continues to be successful in transforming itself out of several 
low margin businesses to higher margin businesses.'' 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	Cisco Systems Inc., up 2 7/16 at 111 11/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Traders were optimistic about the company's earnings, which were  
being released after the close of trading. Cisco reported it earned 
38 cents a share, one penny more than analyst estimates. 

</P>
<P>
	TheStreet.com, trading at 60 1/16, up from an original price of  
19. 
</P>
<P>
	The financial news Web site priced 5.5 million shares late  
Monday at $19 in an initial public offering, up from an original 
pricing of $11 to $13. 

</P>
<P>
	Immunex, up 35 1/8 at 142 1/8.  
</P>
<P>
	The company announced positive clinical data on its arthritis  
drug Enbrel late Monday. 

</P>
<P>
	NeoMagic Corp., down 1 7/16 at 9 11/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Morgan Stanley and Preferred Capital Markets Inc. downgraded the  
stock. Preferred Capital Markets cited possible a shortfall from 
key suppliers to NeoMagic, which makes multimedia attachments for 
notebook computers. 

</P>
<P>
	Comcast Corp., up 1 1/8 at 41 3/8.  
</P>
<P>
	The third-largest cable operator in the country earned 12 cents  
per share in the first quarter, bouncing back from a loss a year 
earlier of 11 cents per share. Comcast attributed the good results 
to expansion into cable markets in Broward County, Fla.; Roseville, 
Calif.; Delaware and Maryland, adding over 20,600 basic customers. 

</P>
</TEXT>
