<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Gonzalez Strains Hamstring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Texas Rangers outfielder Juan Gonzalez left  
Tuesday's game against the Chicago White Sox in the bottom of the 
fourth inning with a slightly strained right hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez left after hitting a solo home run, his eighth of the  
season. He also scored a run after doubling in his first at-bat. 
Gonzalez has 29 RBIs this season, including 22 in the last 17 
games. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, who was replaced by Roberto Kelly, is day to day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
