<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> British Premier League Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEEDS, England (AP) -- Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink scored on a diving  
header with four minutes left Tuesday night to give Leeds a 1-0 
upset win over Arsenal, knocking the Gunners out of first place in 
the Premier League with one game remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	Arsenal (21-4-12), which hadn't lost in the league since Dec.  
13, and Manchester United (21-3-12) each have 75 points. Manchester 
United is ahead of the defending champions on goal difference: 
plus-42 to plus-41. 
</P>
<P>
	Manchester United plays at Blackburn on Wednesday and finishes  
at home Sunday against Derby. Arsenal plays at home Sunday against 
Aston Villa in its final game. 
</P>
<P>
	Leeds looked set to take a 1-0 lead with a minute left in the  
first half, but Ian Harte missed a penalty kick after Arsenal's 
Martin Keown fouled Alan Smith. Harte hit the underside of the 
crossbar, and goalkeeper David Seaman made a tough save on the 
rebound shot from Hasselbaink. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
