<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Maradona Air Rifle Sentence Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) -- Diego Maradona's suspended jail  
sentence for a 1994 incident in which he attacked reporters with an 
air rifle has been reduced by 10 months to 2 years, according to 
news reports. 
</P>
<P>
	Maradona had no immediate comment on the decision by the court  
in Mercedes, 120 miles southwest of Buenos Aires. He can appeal 
that ruling to the province's supreme court. 
</P>
<P>
	A lawyer for the reporters, Marcelo Bermolen, said he was  
pleased with the decision. 
</P>
<P>
	Maradona was accused of using the air rifle to attack reporters  
and photographers outside his country home in 1994. His lawyers 
said he didn't fire the rifle, an argument rejected by prosecutors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
