<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Die in Chemical Plant Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DECATUR, Ala. (AP) -- An explosion at a chemical plant Tuesday  
morning killed two workers and injured two others. 
</P>
<P>
	The explosion rocked the Daikin America chemical plant about 9  
a.m. A fire that resulted was quickly brought under control. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're still trying to figure out what happened,'' said Kathy  
McBee, environmental manager at the plant. 
</P>
<P>
	Killed were Don Prater, 29, and Bonnie Bowling, 41. One employee  
was listed in critical condition and another in fair condition. 
</P>
<P>
	The chemical involved in the blast was tetrafluroethelyne, or  
TFE, a liquid mix of chemicals used to make plastics, according to 
the company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
