<HEADLINE> Oakland's Rogers Hurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Oakland Athletics left-hander Kenny Rogers left  
Tuesday night's game against Detroit in the second inning because 
of back spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	Rogers was hurt while covering first base on Gabe Kapler's  
leadoff grounder. Rogers had to stretch hard to take first baseman 
Jason Giambi's throw for the out and got up limping. 
</P>
<P>
	With the game scoreless, Brad Rigby relieved. Rogers (1-2) was  
coming off his first win of the season, a five-hitter in an 8-2 win 
over Toronto last week. 
</P>
