<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Star Wars Actress: What's the Fuss? </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Swedish actress Pernilla August says she's  
puzzled by all the fuss over the new ``Star Wars'' movie. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think I really get it, what it is about,'' said Ms.  
August, who plays Anakin Skywalker's mother in ``Star Wars: Episode 
I -- The Phantom Menace.'' ``I'm from Sweden and I'm living in the 
countryside with my kids. Really -- I don't know the consequences of 
this.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. August didn't see the original movie when it was first  
released. But she went last year with one of her daughters when the 
remastered version came out. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was fantastic,'' she said Sunday. ``It's not a normal  
audience. It's a happening, something people shared together.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
