<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Referee for Historic Ali Fight Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Lucien ``Pay'' Joubert Sr., the referee of  
the 1978 Muhammad Ali-Leon Spinks heavyweight title fight at the 
Superdome, has died of complications from a stroke. He was 74. 
</P>
<P>
	Joubert died Sunday at Lakeview Regional Medical Center in  
Covington. 
</P>
<P>
	Joubert worked the fight in which Ali regained the title from  
Spinks, and became the first to win the heavyweight crown for a 
third time. 
</P>
<P>
	A funeral Mass will be held Wednesday at Lake Lawn Metairie  
Funeral Home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
