<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-11 08:35:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Wash. Tour Bus Crashes, Injuring 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Nine people were injured Monday a half-mile  
from the White House in a fiery tour bus accident that involved an 
armored truck and three cars, said a District of Columbia Fire 
Department official. 
</P>
<P>
	None of the injuries is believed to be life-threatening, said  
Battalion Chief William Mould. An emergency room doctor at George 
Washington University Hospital said people treated there suffered 
mostly bumps and bruises. 
</P>
<P>
	Mould said witnesses helped save the lives of the seven people  
on the bus -- a tourist family and the driver -- by getting the 
injured out quickly before the propane-powered vehicle burst into 
flames. The family on the Old Town Trolley Tours bus consisted of 
two parents, two grandparents, and two children, he said. Their 
identities were not released. 
</P>
<P>
	The tour company operates a fleet of buses that tour Washington  
landmarks. The small wood and Fiberglas vehicle, designed to 
resemble an early 20th-century trolley car, collided with a car in 
northwest Washington before striking a stopped armored car and two 
parked vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
	``In less than 30 seconds the entire bus was engulfed in  
flames,'' said an unidentified eyewitness who helped pull victims 
off the damaged bus. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to those on the bus, the armored truck driver was  
injured, and a man in a parked truck nearby said he was injured by 
flying glass, Mould said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
