<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pitchers With Same Name Start Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Bobby M. Jones of the Colorado Rockies and Bobby  
J. Jones of the New York Mets made history Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The two became the first pitchers with the same first and last  
names to start against each other in more than 100 years. 
</P>
<P>
	According to the Elias Sports Bureau, baseball's statistician,  
the last duel between starting pitchers sharing the same name was 
April 16, 1899, when Cincinnati's John B. Taylor met Chicago's John 
W. Taylor. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1876, George H. Bradley of Boston and George W. Bradley of  
St. Louis started against each other twice. G.W. Bradley started 
all 64 of St. Louis' games that year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
