<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Higher; Gold Up Also </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was higher against most other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold was also higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0736, down from $1.0747 Monday. The  
dollar was quoted at 120.66 Japanese yen, down from 121.07. At 
midday in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0720 and the dollar 
was quoted at 120.92 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Monday: 1.4972 Swiss  
francs, up from 1.4960; 1.4518 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4609. 
The British pound was quoted at $1.6207, down from $1.6262. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8217 German marks, up from 1.8199; 
6.1099 French francs, up from 6.1036; 2.0526 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.0505; 1,803.53 Italian lire, up from 1,801.68. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $279.00 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$278.00 on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $278.95, up from $278.36.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $2.10 in Hong Kong to close at $278.55.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.40 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.42. 
</P>
