<HEADLINE> Bonilla Put on 15-Day Disabled List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- An errant pitch by Colorado's Pedro Astacio has  
sent New York Mets outfielder Bobby Bonilla to the 15-day disabled 
list. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonilla was placed on the DL Tuesday with a bruised left knee.  
Astacio hit him in the knee in the second inning of Colorado's 10-3 
win Monday night, prompting Bonilla to take a step toward the 
mound. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonilla, 36, left the game after flying out in the fourth  
inning. He was already playing with a partially torn ligament in 
his right knee. Bonilla is hitting just .157 (11-for-70) with two 
homers and 11 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	To take Bonilla's place on the roster, the Mets purchased the  
contract of outfielder Benny Agbayani from Triple-A Norfolk. 
</P>
<P>
	Agbayani, 27, was in Denver for Tuesday night's game against the  
Rockies. He hit .356 with eight homers and 32 RBIs in 28 games with 
Norfolk. 
</P>
<P>
	Agbayani played in 11 games with the Mets last season, going  
2-for-15 with one run scored. 
</P>
