<HEADLINE> Bus Accidents in Past Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Accidents involving buses on highways during past year:  
</P>
<P>
	May 2: A church bus hit by a trailer being towed crashed on U.S.  
82 in New Mexico, killing six teen-age girls from Texas returning 
from a church retreat in central New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	April 30: A bus carrying deaf children to a spelling bee flipped  
over on a highway in Braidwood, Ill., killing a father. 
</P>
<P>
	April 3: A bus carrying high school students from a tour of  
Canada went off an interstate in Lima, Ohio, injuring 34 people. 
</P>
<P>
	March 30: A bus loaded with fifth-graders returning from a trip  
to Sea World collided with a truck carrying strawberries in Nipton, 
Calif., injuring 40 people. 
</P>
<P>
	March 2: A charter bus crashed north of Santa Fe, N.M., killing  
a child and a chaperone returning from a ski outing. 
</P>
<P>
	Dec. 24: A bus bound from New York to Atlantic City, N.J.,  
skidded off the Garden State Parkway, killing eight and injuring 
16. In the two weeks that followed, three more casino-bound buses 
crashed, although no one else was killed. 
</P>
<P>
	Sept. 26, 1998: Two people were killed and 31 others were  
hospitalized when a tour bus crashed on a highway in the Sierra 
Nevada Mountains in Truckee, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	June 20, 1998: A Greyhound bus headed for Pittsburgh slammed  
into a tractor-trailer parked along the Pennsylvania Turnpike in 
Decorum, Pa., killing seven people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
